import { useState } from "react" import styles from './PostGame.module.css' import { validateDescription, validateGameName, validateRelease, validateImage, validateStores, validateDevs, validateGenres, validateTags, sendPost} from "./Functions" import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom'; function PostGame(){ const navigate = useNavigate() const [form, setForm ]= useState({ name: '', description: '', released: '', rating: '', background_image:'', platforms:'', stores: '', developer: '', genres: '', tags:'', playtime: '', }) const [error, setError] = useState({ name: '', description: '', released: '', rating: '', background_image: '', platforms: '', stores: '', developer: '', genres: '', tags:'', playtime: '', }) function handleSubmit(event){ event.preventDefault() sendPost(form) navigate('/home') } function handleChange(event){ const property = event.target.name; const value = event.target.value setForm({...form, [property]: value}) switch(property){ case 'name': return validateGameName({...form, [property]: value}, error, setError) case 'description': return validateDescription({...form, [property]: value}, error, setError) case 'release': return validateRelease({...form, [property]: value}, error, setError) case 'background_image': return validateImage({...form, [property]: value}, error, setError) case 'stores': return validateStores({...form, [property]: value}, error, setError) case 'developer': return validateDevs({...form, [property]: value}, error, setError) case 'genres': return validateGenres({...form, [property]: value}, error, setError) case 'tags': return validateTags({...form, [property]: value}, error, setError) } } return(
{error.name} {error.description} {error.released} {error.background_image} {error.stores} {error.developer} {error.genres} {error.tags}
) } export default PostGame
